# Environment Variables for AI Research Orchestrator

IMPORTANT: This file is for DOCUMENTATION ONLY.
The application uses a secure client-side API key input system.
API keys are stored encrypted (AES-GCM) in the browser's IndexedDB vault.

DO NOT commit actual API keys to version control!

## Runtime (browser UI — not Vite env)

| Setting            | Where                         | Notes                                              |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| Gemini API key     | Settings → AI Configuration   | 39 chars, prefix `AIza`; required for all AI flows |
| Optional NCBI key  | Settings → AI Configuration   | Encrypted vault; higher PubMed rate limits         |
| Output language    | Settings → AI                 | Synthesis language (EN/DE/…)                       |

## Developer / tooling

```bash
# Node environment (set by Vite / CI)
# NODE_ENV=development

# DevContainer: skip Playwright browser download
# SKIP_PLAYWRIGHT=true
```

## Deprecated

- Embedding Gemini keys in `.env` / `VITE_*` is unsupported and insecure for this SPA
  (Vite exposes `VITE_*` to the client bundle).

See `SECURITY.md` and `docs/adr/0003-security-model-client-side-keys.md`.
